subSubSection.paragraph:
Description (based on neotype of
H. extenuata
).

Body with 43 segments. At anterior end (
Fig. 15A
), prostomium bilobed, with distinct cephalic peaks; ceratophore of median antenna in anterior notch, lateral antennae inserted ventrally, styles of antennae papillate, abruptly tapering subdistally to filiform tip; anterior pair of eyes situated dorsolaterally at widest part of prostomium, posterior pair dorsally near hind margin of prostomium; palps papillate, tapering.

Fifteen pairs of elytra, covering dorsum, on segments 2, 4, 5, 7, then on every second segment to 23, 26, 29, 32; last eleven segments cirrigerous; elytral margin and adjacent surface with short, scattered papillae; surface covered by conical microtubercles; macrotubercles drop-shaped, often with brownish pigment (in ethanol), in a row near posterior margin (
Fig. 15B,C
). Cirrigerous segments with distinct dorsal tubercles; dorsal cirri with cylindrical cirrophore, style papillate, abruptly tapering subdistally to filiform tip.

Parapodia biramous; notopodia with elongate acicular lobe; neuropodia with elongate prechaetal acicular lobe with digitiform supra-acicular process; neuropodial postchaetal lobe shorter than prechaetal lobe, rounded; tips of noto- and neuroacicula penetrating epidermis (
Fig. 15D
). Notochaetae stouter than neurochaetae, with distinct rows of spines and blunt tip (
Fig. 15E,F
); neurochaetae with distinct rows of spines, mostly bidentate with distinct secondary tooth, some upper and lower unidentate (
Fig. 15G–J
).
